commits.message: Ignore local dev env script

Refactor code into separate files

So we can make it easier to read
Document the SHINKANSEN_API_HOST in README
Fix references to logging -> app.logger
Add option to specify a sender email
Fix warning about max amount in new payout form

Allow to set a max amount for payouts

So we can help a partner with final checks on prod without moving
significant amounts of money

Handle Shinkansen's messages

We now update the payout status and response contents when Shinkansen
calls us back.

payload.description: Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message: Bump version to 0.6.0
Add verification of incoming responses

Add support for responses (only payouts for now)

Now we can parse responses for payouts. It's written in an extensible
way so we support responses for other transactions (such as those
related to certificates)
Add dummy endpoint to receive shinkansen messages

Change deploy command to include both tamagotchis

(A partner bank wanted their own testing toy)

Rearrange env variables in README

So the required ones appear first
Add default legal name to README
Update python-shinkansen to 0.5.2

payload.description: Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message: Bump version to 0.5.2
Handle 400 error code without json body

Add more customization via env vars

Now you can set the sender's legal name. Also useful for end-to-end
testing.

Add more env vars to customize sender details.

We now allow to set a custom RUT (CLID) and a custom account number.
This is useful to use tamagotchi for end-to-end tests with arbitrary
credentials.

Update jwcrypto and python-shinkansen

So we stop depending on a vulnerable jwcrypto (even though we are not
affected by the vulnerability)

payload.description: Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message:
Update to jwcrypto 1.4.x

1.3.x has a security vulnerability which doesn't impact our usage.

That said, it's better to not depend on vulnerable libs.
Bump version to 0.5.1

Avoid trailing slash in API base_url

It doesn't break anything, but still better to avoid double slashes.

Allow to change the sender in messages.

This way this codebase can be used to test signatures or certificates
for participants different to tamagotchi itself.
Rename README to reflect we use markdown format

comment.body: Está live esta versión en http://tamagotchi.fly.dev/

payload.description: Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message: Bump version to 0.5.0

Stop importing submodules from main module

It makes python3 -m shinkansen.jws spit out warnings.

And we are not really gaining much since submodules have
verbose/explicit functions/class so and invoking them with
shinkansen.<submodule>.<long_name> is not very nice.
Add a README

payload.description: A toy/sample integration in Python (running an very simple flask app)
A toy/sample integration in Python (running an very simple flask app)
Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message: Fix wrong test command in README
Bump version to 0.4.0
Ignore vscode files
Add requests and requests-mock as deps
Require a lower poetry-core to avoid weird errors

Rename {test_shinkansen,_jws}

We'll need separate test files for each module

Add payouts support

- Includes simple classes to create and send payout message
- ...and to also handle the immediate HTTP response.
- Support for Shinkansen's actual async response is not implemented yet
- Some reorganization in the code to move common stuff to its own module
  thus avoiding circular imports
